, people of color, workers, ill and disabled people, and queer and gender nonconforming people. Against this history of barriers and assaults, Bans, Walls, Raids, Sanctuary mounts a rallying cry for a broad-based, abolitionist sanctuary movement for all.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aIllegal aliensxGovernment policyzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aSanctuary movementzUnited Statesy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  abarriers.  ablack.  aborder wall.  aborders.  acitizens.  adaca.  adisability.  adisabled people.  adiscrimination.  adonald trump.  aethnicity.  agender violence.  ahistory.  aice raids.  aice.  aillegal immigration.  aimmigrants.  aimmigration.  amaga.  amass incarceration.  amigrants.  amuslim ban.  anoncitizens.  anonconforming people.  anonfiction.  apolitics.  aprejudice.  apresident.  arace.  aracism.  arefugees.  asanctuary.  asexual assault.  asocial issues.  asocial science.  atrump presidency.  awhite house.  axenophobia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520973268zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520973268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520973268.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press 